notes:

run server.js from terminal => 
server starts reading database, connects to port using express => 
server runs the script files (or everything in the public folder) using express(static) =>
browser runs the html file =>
feedback taken from listener buttons on client-side script => 
sent to server side via fetch, code executed based on routers matched 



Heroku steps: 

- installed Heroku (software that runs things on a virtual computer)
- launched website, by "deploying" with node: 
https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/deploying-nodejs#deploy-your-application-to-heroku
or
https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/getting-started-with-nodejs?singlepage=true

- make sure all the app dependencies are declared on package.json 
	- heroku create
	- git push heroku master

PostgresQL database steps: 
- 


heroku addons:create heroku-postgresql:hobby-dev
npm install pg
